{"name": "range-typed-integers", "metadata": {"name": "range-typed-integers", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Integer type aliases that specify valid value ranges.", "upload_time": 1653652104}, "documentation": ["# Range-Typed Integers\n\nThis package provides integer types that have a specific range of valid values.\n\n## Usage\n\nThe package provides some types (as [NewType]) that represent their respective [Rust integer type]:\n`u8`, `u16`, `u32`, `u64`, `i8`, `i16`, `i32` and `i64`:\n\n```\nfrom range_typed_integers import u8, i8\n\n# u8 is an unsigned 8-bit integer so its range is 0-255:\na: u8 = 12  # valid\na: u8 = -12  # invalid - The type checker should mark this as an error.\na: u8 = 900  # invalid - The type checker should mark this as an error.\n```\n\nThe types are defined as `NewTypes` of `ValueRange` annotated integers. This is also how\nyou can define your own custom ranged integer types. As an example this is literally how\n`range_typed_integers.i8` is defined:\n\n```\nfrom typing import Annotated, NewType\nfrom range_typed_integers import ValueRange\n\ni8 = NewType('i8', Annotated[int, ValueRange(-128, 127)])\n```\n\nTo cast values to typed integers, you can:\n\n- use the NewType's constructor: `i8(12)`\n- Use the \"checked constructors\": `i8_checked(12)`.\n  These will raise a `IntegerBoundError` if the value is out of range (subclass of `OverflowError`).\n- use the [cast] function: `cast(i8, 12)`\n\n## Runtime checking\n\nYou can use the function `check_int` to check if an integer fits into any integer type.:\n\n```\n>>> from range_typed_integers import check_int, u8\n>>>\n>>> class A\n...     field: u8\n...\n>>> # You can use this directly with a type.\n>>> check_int(u8, 0)\nTrue\n>>> check_int(u8, -1)\nFalse\n>>> # Or have the function look up the type annotations for an attribute on an object.\n>>> check_int((A, 'field'), 0)\nTrue\n>>> check_int((A, 'field'), 256)\nFalse\n>>> # You can also use this with non-ranged integers (will always return True).\n>>> check_int(int, 1234567)\nTrue\n>>> # Or even arbitrary types (will always return True and do no type validation).\n>>> check_int(str, 1234)\nTrue\n```\n\nFor ease-of-use the types shipped with this package, also have \"checked constructors\" (eg. `u8_checked`),\nthat will cast a value to their type and raise an `IntegerBoundError` if the value is out of range.\n\n## MyPy and Python Support\n\nThis is only truly supported in Python 3.9+, due to the lack of the `Annotated` type in earlier versions.\n\nHowever 3.8 is also supported via `typing_extensions`. Note however, that MyPy with Python 3.8 will not accept\n`Annotated` as a type to use with `NewType`.\n\n[cast]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#typing.cast\n[mypy]: https://mypy.readthedocs.io/\n[newtype]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/typing.html#newtype\n[rust integer type]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch03-02-data-types.html#integer-types\n"], "modules": [{"name": "range_typed_integers", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "range_typed_integers.check_int", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.check_int", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.CheckIntWarning", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.CheckIntWarning", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.get_range", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.get_range", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i16", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.i16", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i16_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.i16_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i32", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.i32", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i32_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.i32_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i64", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.i64", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i64_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.i64_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i8", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.i8", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.i8_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.i8_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.IntegerBoundError", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.IntegerBoundError", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u16", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.u16", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u16_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.u16_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u32", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.u32", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u32_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.u32_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u64", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.u64", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u64_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.u64_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u8", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.u8", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.u8_checked", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.check.u8_checked", "project": null}}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.ValueRange", "xref": {"fqname": "range_typed_integers.types.ValueRange", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "range_typed_integers.types", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"n